<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
- 
<bibRefCitation author="Jordan, MA" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia, Turriers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B24" refString="Jordan, MA, 1851. Pugillus plantarum novarum. Memoires de l'Academie Royale des Sciences, Belles-Lettres et Arts de Lyon, ser. 2, section des sciences 1: 212-358." title="Pugillus plantarum novarum. Memoires de l'Academie Royale des Sciences, Belles-Lettres et Arts de Lyon, ser. 2, section des sciences 1: 212 - 358." year="1851">Jordan (1851</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jordan, MA" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia, Turriers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B25" refString="Jordan, MA, 1856. Notices sur plusieurs plantes nouvelles in Billot PC, Annotations a la Flora de France ed d'Allemagne. Edler, Haguenau, 43-49." title="Notices sur plusieurs plantes nouvelles in Billot PC, Annotations a la Flora de France ed d'Allemagne. Edler, Haguenau, 43 - 49." year="1856">1856</bibRefCitation>
) believed that the plants referred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Godron, M" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences, Lettres et arts de Nancy" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B18" refString="Godron, M, 1847. Observations sur le Dianthus virgineus de Linne. Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences, Lettres et arts de Nancy 1846: 1 - 16" title="Observations sur le Dianthus virgineus de Linne." volume="1846" year="1847">Godron (1847</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Godron, M" editor="Grenier, M" journalOrPublisher="1. J. - B. Bailliere, Paris et De Sainte-Agathe Aine Besancon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="228 - 242" refId="B19" refString="Godron, M, 1848. Dianthus. In: Grenier, M, Godron, M, Eds., Flore de France ou description des plantes qui croissent naturellement en France et en Corse. 1. J.-B. Bailliere, Paris et De Sainte-Agathe Aine Besancon: 228 - 242" title="Dianthus." volumeTitle="Flore de France ou description des plantes qui croissent naturellement en France et en Corse." year="1848">1848</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<taxonomicName family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. virgineus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="virgineus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. virgineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. actually represent a different species, which he renamed 
<taxonomicName family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. godronianus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="godronianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. godronianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Godron, M" editor="Grenier, M" journalOrPublisher="1. J. - B. Bailliere, Paris et De Sainte-Agathe Aine Besancon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="228 - 242" refId="B19" refString="Godron, M, 1848. Dianthus. In: Grenier, M, Godron, M, Eds., Flore de France ou description des plantes qui croissent naturellement en France et en Corse. 1. J.-B. Bailliere, Paris et De Sainte-Agathe Aine Besancon: 228 - 242" title="Dianthus." volumeTitle="Flore de France ou description des plantes qui croissent naturellement en France et en Corse." year="1848">Godron (1848)</bibRefCitation>
, this species grows in the surroundings of Montpellier, South France, and Corsica. A duplicate of the collection no. 959 by Soleirol, explicitly cited as seen by 
<bibRefCitation author="Godron, M" editor="Grenier, M" journalOrPublisher="1. J. - B. Bailliere, Paris et De Sainte-Agathe Aine Besancon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="228 - 242" refId="B19" refString="Godron, M, 1848. Dianthus. In: Grenier, M, Godron, M, Eds., Flore de France ou description des plantes qui croissent naturellement en France et en Corse. 1. J.-B. Bailliere, Paris et De Sainte-Agathe Aine Besancon: 228 - 242" title="Dianthus." volumeTitle="Flore de France ou description des plantes qui croissent naturellement en France et en Corse." year="1848">Godron (1848)</bibRefCitation>
, was chosen as lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This specimen corresponds with the protologue and with the current application of the name. In 
<bibRefCitation author="Kerguelen, M" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia, Turriers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Kerguelen, M, 1993. Index synonymique de la flore de France. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris." title="Index synonymique de la flore de France. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris." year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(1993)
</bibRefCitation>
, this taxon is considered accepted at varietal rank (
<taxonomicName family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. sylvestris subsp. var. var. godronianus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="variety" species="sylvestris" subSpecies="var." variety="godronianus">D. sylvestris subsp. longicaulis var. godronianus</taxonomicName>
). In 
<bibRefCitation author="Jauzein, Ph" editor="Tison, JM" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia, Turriers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1114 - 1121" refId="B23" refString="Jauzein, Ph, 2014. Dianthus. In: Tison, JM, Jauzein, Ph, Michaud, H, Eds., Flore de la France mediterraneenne continentale. Naturalia, Turriers: 1114 - 1121" title="Dianthus." volumeTitle="Flore de la France mediterraneenne continentale." year="2014">Jauzein (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, this taxon is instead included in 
<taxonomicName family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. caryophyllus subsp. longicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subSpecies" species="caryophyllus" subSpecies="longicaulis">D. caryophyllus subsp. longicaulis</taxonomicName>
(Ten.) Arcang., but the author argues that it could constitute a distinct subspecies (
<taxonomicName family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. caryophyllus subsp. godronianus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subSpecies" species="caryophyllus" subSpecies="godronianus">D. caryophyllus subsp. godronianus</taxonomicName>
(Jord.) P.Martin). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jordan in Mem. Acad. Roy. Sci. Lyon, Sect. Sci., ser. 2, 1: 241. 1851. [January" authorityYear="1985" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Dianthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dianthus godronianus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="godronianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dianthus godronianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is instead considered a distinct species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tison, J-M" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B37" refString="Tison, J-M, de Foucault, B, 2014. Flora Gallica. Flore de France. Biotope Editons, Meze." title="Flora Gallica. Flore de France. Biotope Editons, Meze." year="2014">Tison and de Foucault (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, although these authors note that some coastal populations in Provence differ for a few morphological features. According to the lectotype features and the recent lectotypification of the latter name (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" author="Domina, G" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1096 - 1100" refId="B15" refString="Domina, G, Astuti, G, Barone, G, Gargano, D, Minuto, L, Varaldo, L, Peruzzi, L, 2021. Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae). Taxon 70 (5): 1096 - 1100, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" title="Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" volume="70" year="2021">Domina et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
), this species can be regarded as a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. virgineus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="virgineus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. virgineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
